      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WAR DAN PHOENIX (1) has the hoof on the till after finishing runner-up in his last three outings, the last two from this barrier. Led and fought well to miss narrowly at Kilmore last week. Can break through. MISS MUSCLE (5) made an encouraging debut when she started favourite and fought well to go under narrowly as runner-up at Terang. Similar draw and is open to natural improvement. LEZAMA (3) is working towards a win having placed in his last two outings. Draws lower than in both of those attempts and should be hitting peak fitness now. PIPALICIOUS (6) was tackling stronger opposition at the end of last campaign but went close a few times earlier in the prep and was readied with a solid trial. MI BOW (2) is a long time maiden but has only once missed the placings in her last six starts and draws to be competitive again.",
